<!-- ##### SECTION Title ##### -->
gtkglwidget

<!-- ##### SECTION Short_Description ##### -->
OpenGL extension API to GtkWidget.

<!-- ##### SECTION Long_Description ##### -->
<para>
GtkGLExt is an extension to Gtk 2.0 or above which adds OpenGL
capabilities to any gtk widget. As opposed to Jane Loff's gtkglarea,
It does not provide any OpenGL widget, but an interface to use opengl
on any widget. Its use is quite simple: use
#gtk_widget_set_gl_capability to add OpenGL support to a widget, it
will create a GLcontext and a gldrawable for the widget, which can be
obtained via #gtk_widget_get_gl_context and
#gtk_widget_get_gl_drawable. With them, gdk_gl_drawable_gl_begin and
gdk_gl_drawable_gl_end can be called. Between those two function,
OpenGL function calls can be made.
</para>

