</para>

<!-- ##### FUNCTION gtk_widget_set_gl_capability ##### -->
<para>
Prepares the widget for its use with OpenGL, by creating the
gl_context and the gl_drawable, which are afterwards obtainable by
#gtk_widget_get_gl_context and #gtk_widget_get_gl_drawable.
</para>

@widget: The widget to be added OpenGL capabilities.
@glconfig: OpenGL configuration, see gdk_gl_config_new.
@share_list: Sometimes is useful to have several widgets displaying similar information (f.e: different views of the same object=. This parameter allows two widgets to share display lists. Insert here the GdkGLcontext of the widget to share lists with, or NULL to share no lists.
@direct: Usually direct rendering is desired (i.e: use of hardware rendering), but this is not always required, use this to select among direct or indirect rendering.
@render_type: GDK_GL_RGBA_TYPE or GDK_COLOR_INDEX_TYPE (currently unused)
@Returns: TRUE if succesful, FALSE otherwise.


<!-- ##### FUNCTION gtk_widget_is_gl_capable ##### -->
<para>
This function is useful to check if a widget is OpenGL-capable (i.e if
it is possible to use OpenGL functions to draw on it).
</para>

@widget: Widget to check for capability
@Returns: TRUE if the widget is OpenGL-capable, FALSE otherwise.


<!-- ##### FUNCTION gtk_widget_get_gl_config ##### -->
<para>
This returns a GdkGLConfig with the OpenGL configuration of the widget.
</para>

@widget: Widget to check for OpenGL configuration.
@Returns: A GdkGLConfig with the OpenGL configuration of the widget.


<!-- ##### FUNCTION gtk_widget_get_gl_context ##### -->
<para>
Returns the GdkGLContext holded by the widget. This struct is needed
for the function gdk_gl_drawable_begin, or for sharing Displaylists
(see #gtk_widget_set_gl_capability.
</para>

@widget: Widget to obtain GdkGLContext from.
@Returns: The GdkGLContext of the widget.


<!-- ##### FUNCTION gtk_widget_get_gl_window ##### -->
<para>
Returns the pointer to the GdkGLWindow struct of the widget.
</para>

@widget: The widget owner of the GdkGLWindow.
@Returns: The pointer to the GdkGLWindow


<!-- ##### MACRO gtk_widget_get_gl_drawable ##### -->
<para>
Return the #GdkGLDrawable holded by the #GtkWidget. In fact it calls
#gtk_widget_get_gl_window and casts result to a GDK_GL_DRAWABLE.
</para>

@widget: a #GtkWidget.
@Returns: the #GdkGLDrawable.


